	<LINE>card, which is open to inspection, may have a letter</LINE>
	<LINE>written or printed upon it, any card whatever, and</LINE>
	<LINE>even any piece of paper, if only it be placed in an open</LINE>
	<LINE>wrapper, may be sent through the post with a letter</LINE>
	<LINE>written or printed upon it for a postage of a halfpenny.</LINE>
